Not all Flyweight subclasses need to be shared. The Flyweight interface enables sharing; it doesn't
enforce it. It's common for UnsharedConcreteFlyweight objects to have ConcreteFlyweight objects as
children at some level in the flyweight object structure.

object supplies an existing instance or creates one, if none exists.
